SPV Privacy Policy
1. Information We Collect
When you use this application, we may collect the following information:

(1). Information You Provide Voluntarily
   - Photos and videos you import and save (stored locally on your device only, not uploaded to any server).
   - App password, hidden space content, and icon settings.

(2). Device Permissions and Functional Use
   - Photo Library Access: To import and save photos and videos.
   - Camera and Microphone Access: For capturing photos and recording videos, enabled only when you choose to use it.
   - Face ID/Touch ID: For authentication and security protection.
   - Location Access: Used only when you enable related features, no background tracking.
   - Network Access: For in-app purchases (IAP) and necessary service requests.

(3). Automatically Collected Information
   - Device information (such as model, OS version, unique device identifier).
   - App usage logs (such as crash reports, used only to improve user experience).

Important Notice:
- Your photos and videos remain stored on your device and are never uploaded, shared, or sold.
- Currently, the app does not integrate any advertising SDKs.

2. How We Use Information
The collected information is used for the following purposes:
- To provide import, storage, and security features for photos and videos.
- To support security features such as app password, Face ID authentication, hidden space, and intruder alerts.
- To process and verify in-app purchases (IAP).
- To improve product performance and enhance user experience.

3. Data Storage and Protection
- Your photos, videos, and private data are stored only on your local device and are not uploaded to any server.
- The app uses system-level encryption and security measures (such as Face ID and password protection) to safeguard your data.
- If you uninstall the app, all related data will be deleted unless you have backed it up manually.

4. Third-Party Services
- This app may use Apple's in-app purchase (IAP) services for payment and verification.
- The app does not currently use third-party advertising or analytics SDKs. If this changes in the future, we will update this Privacy Policy and notify you.

5. Your Rights
In accordance with applicable laws (including China’s Personal Information Protection Law, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)), you have the following rights:
- Right of Access: You can view and access data stored in the app.
- Right of Rectification: You can modify or delete files and settings stored in the app.
- Right of Deletion: You can uninstall the app or clear data within the app at any time.
- Right to Restrict Processing (GDPR): You may limit how we process your data.
- Right to Withdraw Consent: You may revoke permissions (e.g., photo library, location, Face ID) in your device settings at any time.

6. Children’s Privacy
This app is not intended for children under the age of 13 (as required by COPPA in the U.S.) or under the age of 16 (as required by GDPR in the EU).
If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected information from a minor, we will take immediate steps to delete it.

7. International Users
- For Users in China: We comply with the Personal Information Protection Law (PIPL).
- For Users in the United States: We comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).
- For Users in the European Union: We comply with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and ensure proper safeguards for data processing and cross-border transfers.

8. Updates to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our services or legal requirements. Updates will be published in the app and will take effect immediately.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or personal data protection, please contact us:

- Email: a26225737@gmail.com
